  • Class Summary
    Class
    Description
    KCore<K,​VV,​EV>
    The class KCore computes the coreness of each vertex in the graph under K-Core model.
    KCore.DegreeMap<K>
    map the degree of each vertex into dataset
    KCore.KCoreMessenger<K,​EV>
    distributes the current coreness to neighbors
    KCore.KCoreUpdater<K,​EV>
    update the coreness of a vertex by its neighbors i.e., find the largest k such that the number of neighbors with coreness >= k is no less than k
    KTruss<VV,​EV>
    The class KTruss computes the truss number of each edge in the graph under K-Truss model.
    KTruss.DuplicatePLEdge
    duplicate PL edges
    KTruss.EdgeWithCount
    sort the id of each edge
    KTruss.KTrussDataMap
    map truss number of each edge into dataset
    KTruss.KTrussMessenger<EV>
    distributes the current trussness to neighbors
    KTruss.KTrussUpdater
    iteratively update the truss number of every PL vertex until convergence
    KTruss.SupportToKTrussData
    map the support number into each edge
    KTruss.TriagnleToEdgeWithCount
    split three edges in each triangle
    KTruss.TriagnleToPLEdge
    save triangles to PL edges
    KTruss.TriangleSort
    sort the id of vertices of each triangle
    MaximalClique<VV,​EV>
    The class MaximalClique enumerate all maximal clique in the graph.
    MaximalClique.CliqueFlatMap<K>

    MaximalClique.CliqueMessager<EV>

    MaximalClique.VertexMap<K,​VV>
